Here&#39;s an example of query with AND, OR and NOT:

    GET cities/_search
    {
      &quot;query&quot;: {&quot;bool&quot;: {&quot;must&quot;: [
        {&quot;bool&quot;: {&quot;should&quot;: [
          {&quot;bool&quot;: {&quot;must&quot;: [
            {&quot;match&quot;: {&quot;description&quot;: &quot;great&quot;}},
            {&quot;match&quot;: {&quot;description&quot;: &quot;orange&quot;}}
          ]}},
          {&quot;match&quot;: {&quot;description&quot;: &quot;popular&quot;}}
        ]}},

        {&quot;bool&quot;: {&quot;must_not&quot;: [
          {&quot;match&quot;: {&quot;description&quot;: &quot;poor&quot;}}
        ]}},

        {&quot;bool&quot;: {&quot;should&quot;: [
          {&quot;match&quot;: {&quot;city&quot;: &quot;London&quot;}},
          {&quot;match&quot;: {&quot;city&quot;: &quot;Paris&quot;}},
        ]}}
      ]}},
    &quot;size&quot;: 20,
    &quot;from&quot;: 0
    }

It searches among specified cities only cities, which description includes (&quot;great&quot; AND &quot;orange&quot;) OR &quot;popular&quot; words but excludes results, where &quot;poor&quot; word found

`must` means **AND**, `should` means **OR**, `must_not` means **NOT**

Other examples you can find [here][1]:



  [1]: https://www.elastic.co/blog/lost-in-translation-boolean-operations-and-filters-in-the-bool-query

